<p>Neal Ford about technical presentations</p>
<p><a href="http://www.infoq.com/interviews/neal-ford-technical-presentations">http://www.infoq.com/interviews/neal-ford-technical-presentations</a></p>
<p>- Anti-pattern: bullet-riddled corpse</p>
<p>- Tell a story in your presentation (beginning, middle, end)</p>
<p>- Add a cue on the slides that are related (color, symbol)</p>
<p>- Insert a joke/something emotional every 7-10 minutes</p>
<p>- Slides are not expensive. Don't cram everything in as few as possible</p>
<p>- Tape yourself. See if you have a filler word like <i>frankly or umm</i></p>
<p>- </p>
